Activity 7: Managing Files and Creating Roles in Ansible

  1. Objectives:

    1. Manage files in remote servers

    2. Implement roles in ansible

2. Discussion:

In this activity, we look at the concept of copying a file to a server. We are going to create a file into our git repository and use Ansible to grab that file and put it into a particular place so that we could do things like customize a default website, or maybe install a default configuration file. We will also implement roles to consolidate plays.

Task 2: Download a file and extract it to a remote server

  1. Edit the site.yml. Just before the web_servers play, create a new play:

    • hosts: workstations become: true tasks:


      • name: install unzip package:

        name: unzip


      • name: install terraform unarchive:

        src:

        https://releases.hashicorp.com/terraform/0.12.28/terraform_0.12.28_linux_a md64.zip

        dest: /usr/local/bin remote_src: yes

        mode: 0755 owner: root group: root


  2. Edit the inventory file and add workstations group. Add any Ubuntu remote server. Make sure to remember the IP address.


  3. Run the playbook. Describe the output. The terraform is installed on server2.

  4. On the Ubuntu remote workstation, type terraform to verify installation of terraform. Describe the output. After issuing the terraform command on sever2, the list of basic commands along with their definition is then displayed, this confirms that terraform has been installed on the machine.

Reflections:


  1. What is the importance of creating roles?

    • In the previous activity we were tasked to perform playbooks implementing tags, we added the constraints on the playbooks using tags on this activity we have performed the same however instead of using tags we have used roles and have divided a single playbook to different directories and has executed the tasks from a single playbook calling the playbooks in the different directory corresponding to the different roles. In this way we can manage multiple machines with different roles such as db_servers, file_servers and even on different operating systems.


  2. What is the importance of managing files?

    • This course which is CPE 232 - Managing enterprise servers revolves around file management on different remote servers. In Database management or in any computer which has multiple files file management is crucial especially on managing a large amount of data. In this case we are managing multiple machines with multiple purposes thus also having multiple operating systems. This improves time and cost effectiveness when it comes to handling multiple machines and servers.

      Conclusion:


    • On this hands-on activity we have managed files in remote servers and have implemented roles mainly file_severs, db_servers, web_servers, workstation and base, in ansible. We have also executed a playbook wherein the directory roles are used to execute numerous playbooks containing a task in the different roles wherein are also located in different directories. With these new skills and knowledge that i have performed on this hands on activity on Systems administration I can assure that i will be able to implement these procedures in future hands-on activities and hopefully soon as a soon to be system administrator.
